PART J — Mixed Bitfield Types (Important Corrected)

Q22
struct e{    unsigned int a:2;    unsigned int b:3;    unsigned int c:5;    char d:2;};
Important:
This is implementation-defined.
Different compilers may pack differently.
Your compiler output:
sizeof = 4
Why?
Compiler packed all fields into same existing storage unit.
Conceptual:
a,b,c,d all fit inside one 32-bit unit

